<p>I had not gone very far when I met my brother on the road in the best of health and looking well. I had tea at the hospital and stayed the night at a private house not very far away.</p>
<p>Tuesday Jan 15. 1918. 1261</p>
<p>This morning I packed up three parcels of post cards to send to Australia, including one of my diaries No. 6. Had a long talk with Willie and had a look around the hospital. It is a very large place and before the war was a lunatic asylum. This afternoon Willie</p>
